    "experimental_design_for_optimization": {
        "ingredients_identification": "Tablets prepared by wet granulation technique using polymers HPMC K4M, HPMC K100M, xanthan gum, and sodium bicarbonate as gas-generating agent. Binder solution was PVP K-30 in isopropyl alcohol.",
        "preparation_method_summary": "Dry ingredients were passed through 0.425 mm sieve, geometrically mixed, and blended. PVP K-30 binder solution in IPA was added with kneading to form homogeneous mass. Dough mass was passed through 2.0 mm sieve, granules dried at room temperature, then passed through 1.18 mm sieve. Granules were lubricated with magnesium stearate and talc, and compressed.",
        "results_summary": "Formulations exhibited controlled drug release, non-Fickian diffusion mechanism. 038_F4 was best overall (HPMC K4M based). 038_F9 best with HPMC K100M. 038_F16 best with xanthan gum. In vivo study on 038_F4 showed gastric retention time of 180±30 min.",
        "equation": "\\[\\frac{M_{\\mathrm{t}}}{M_{\\mathrm{m}}} = bt^n\\] (Korsmeyer-Peppas equation for release mechanism)",
        "absorbance_wavelength": "278 nm"
    },
